#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:231
msgid "From right to left, the following status indicators are available:"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:234
msgid "Loading Indicator: The LED becomes yellow when an image is getting loaded and turns green after loading is successfully done. If there are problems with loading the image, it turns red."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:239
msgid "Resolution: Image resolution in pixels. 4656x3520 in the screenshot above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:242
msgid "Zoom Percentage. 13% above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:244
msgid "Cartesian Coordinates: Displays and updates the current mouse position as you hover over the image. X:769 Y:3508 above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:248
msgid "Pixel Value: Value of the pixel under the mouse. 1,792 above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:251
msgid "Equatorial Coordinates: If the image contains a valid WCS header, the J2000 Right Ascension (RA) and declination (DE) values are displayed. 13h 14' 22\" 42 37' 35\" above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:256
msgid "Image Stats: Displays the HFR, Eccentricity and number of stars if computed. HFR:1.96 Ecc:0.43 143 stars above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:260
msgid "Clipped Stars: If Show Clipping is activated in the main toolbar, it displays the number of possibly clipped pixels. Clip:403 above."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:264
msgid "In addition to image display, the viewer can process World-Coordinate-System (WCS) header if present within the FITS file and provides useful information regarding the objects found within the image, equatorial grid overlay, popup menu, and the ability to slew the mount (if connected) to any point within the image."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:271
msgid "Several filters can be applied to enhance the image include auto stretch and high contrast. Depending on the image size, these operations can take a few seconds to complete. The bottom status bar displays the current pixel value and current X & Y coordinates of the mouse pointer within the image. Furthermore, it includes the current zoom level and the image resolution."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:279
msgid "When loading a bayered image, the viewer can automatically debayer the image if *Auto Debayer* is checked in the FITS Settings. The debayering operation fetches the bayer pattern (e.g. RGGB) from the FITS header. If none exists, you can alter the debayering algorithm and pattern from the ``File`` menu or by using the **Ctrl**\\ +\\ **D** shortcut."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/fitsviewer-main-controls.rst:286
msgid "Since operations such as auto debayering and auto WCS are computationally expensive and stress the processor on low-powered embedded devices, you can toggle their behavior in :doc:`KStars Settings FITS page <fits-configure>`."
msgstr ""

